{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd92-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"30118"},"text":"§ 30118.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Notification of defects and noncompliance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd93-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Notification by Secretary","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Transportation shall notify the manufacturer of a motor vehicle or replacement equipment immediately after making an initial decision (through testing, inspection, investigation, or research carried out under this chapter, examining communications under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s30166/f"},"text":"section 30166(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":", or otherwise) that the vehicle or equipment contains a defect related to motor vehicle safety or does not comply with an applicable motor vehicle safety standard prescribed under this chapter. The notification shall include the information on which the decision is based. The Secretary shall publish a notice of each decision under this subsection in the Federal Register. Subject to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s30167/a"},"text":"section 30167(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the notification and information are available to any interested person."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd94-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Defect and Noncompliance Proceedings and Orders","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd95-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary may make a final decision that a motor vehicle or replacement equipment contains a defect related to motor vehicle safety or does not comply with an applicable motor vehicle safety standard prescribed under this chapter only after giving the manufacturer an opportunity to present information, views, and arguments showing that there is no defect or noncompliance or that the defect does not affect motor vehicle safety. Any interested person also shall be given an opportunity to present information, views, and arguments.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd96-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" If the Secretary decides under paragraph (1) of this subsection that the vehicle or equipment contains the defect or does not comply, the Secretary shall order the manufacturer to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd97-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" give notification under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s30119"},"text":"section 30119 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to the owners, purchasers, and dealers of the vehicle or equipment of the defect or noncompliance; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd98-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" remedy the defect or noncompliance under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s30120"},"text":"section 30120 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd99-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Notification by Manufacturer","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A manufacturer of a motor vehicle or replacement equipment shall notify the Secretary by certified mail or electronic mail, and the owners, purchasers, and dealers of the vehicle or equipment as provided in section 30119(d) of this section, if the manufacturer—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd9a-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" learns the vehicle or equipment contains a defect and decides in good faith that the defect is related to motor vehicle safety; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd9b-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" decides in good faith that the vehicle or equipment does not comply with an applicable motor vehicle safety standard prescribed under this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd9c-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Exemptions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"On application of a manufacturer, the Secretary shall exempt the manufacturer from this section if the Secretary decides a defect or noncompliance is inconsequential to motor vehicle safety. The Secretary may take action under this subsection only after notice in the Federal Register and an opportunity for any interested person to present information, views, and arguments.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd9d-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Hearings About Meeting Notification Requirements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"On the motion of the Secretary or on petition of any interested person, the Secretary may conduct a hearing to decide whether the manufacturer has reasonably met the notification requirements under this section. Any interested person may make written and oral presentations of information, views, and arguments on whether the manufacturer has reasonably met the notification requirements. If the Secretary decides that the manufacturer has not reasonably met the notification requirements, the Secretary shall order the manufacturer to take specified action to meet those requirements and may take any other action authorized under this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd9e-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Reports on Notification Campaigns.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bd9f-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Each manufacturer that is conducting a campaign under subsection (b) or (c) or any other provision of law (including regulations) to notify manufacturers, distributors, owners, purchasers, or dealers of a defect or noncompliance shall submit to the Administrator of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bda0-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/f/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" by the applicable date described in section 573.7(d) of title 49, Code of Federal Regulations (or a successor regulation), a quarterly report describing the campaign for each of 8 consecutive quarters, beginning with the quarter in which the campaign was initiated; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bda1-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/f/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an annual report for each of the 3 years beginning after the date of completion of the last quarter for which a quarterly report is submitted under subparagraph (A).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bda2-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s30118/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Requirements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, each report under this subsection shall comply with the requirements of section 573.7 of title 49, Code of Federal Regulations (or a successor regulation).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcb48bda3-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272/s1/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/950"},"text":"108 Stat. 950","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/346/s101/a/tIII/s364"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–346, § 101(a) [title III, § 364]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-23"},"text":"Oct. 23, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1356"},"text":"114 Stat. 1356","children":[],"tail":", 1356A–37; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/414/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–414, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1800"},"text":"114 Stat. 1800","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/94/dB/tXXIV/s24104/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–94, div. B, title XXIV, § 24104(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"dat